NAME
    gcloud sql backups restore - restores a backup of a Cloud SQL instance

SYNOPSIS
    gcloud sql backups restore BACKUP_ID --restore-instance=RESTORE_INSTANCE
        [--async] [--backup-instance=BACKUP_INSTANCE] [GCLOUD_WIDE_FLAG ...]

DESCRIPTION
    Restores a backup of a Cloud SQL instance.

POSITIONAL ARGUMENTS
     BACKUP_ID
        The ID of the backup run to restore from.

REQUIRED FLAGS
     --restore-instance=RESTORE_INSTANCE
        Cloud SQL instance ID that will be restored.

OPTIONAL FLAGS
     --async
        Do not wait for the operation to complete.

     --backup-instance=BACKUP_INSTANCE
        The ID of the instance that the backup was taken from.

GCLOUD WIDE FLAGS
    These flags are available to all commands: --account, --configuration,
    --flatten, --format, --help, --log-http, --project, --quiet, --trace-token,
    --user-output-enabled, --verbosity. Run $ gcloud help for details.

NOTES
    This variant is also available:

        $ gcloud beta sql backups restore

